,{"kind":"text","text":"arms or weapons]. (S, O. [In one of my copies of the S,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAlHadiydi","text_ar":"بِالحَدِيدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) [Accord. to the TA, one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino qawomK $uk~aAkK","text_ar":"مِنْ قَوْمٍ شُكَّاكٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN $ak~aAkN","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ شَكَّاكٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ak~aAkN","text_ar":"شَكَّاكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"seems evidently to be a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAk~N","text_ar":"شَاكٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAku Als~ilaAHi","text_ar":"شَاكُ السِّلَاحِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAkiY Als~ilaAHi","text_ar":"شَاكِى السِّلَاحِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in arts."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$wk","text_ar":"شوك"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$kw","text_ar":"شكو"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHimN $aAk~apN","text_ar":"رَحِمٌ شَاكَّةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Near relationship."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA. [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ak~ati Alr~aHimu","text_ar":"شَكَّتِ الرَّحِمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".])       -A2-  See also what next follows."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n22890","headword_ar":"شَاكٍ","root":"$kw and $kY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$akiY~N","text_ar":"شَكِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places.       -A2-  In the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN $aAkiY Als~ilaAHi","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ شَاكِى السِّلَاحِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) which means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man whose weapon is sharp,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whose weapons are sharp,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, *) Akh says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$AkY","text_ar":"شاكى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is formed by transposition from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAy^ik","text_ar":"شَايِك"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v. in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$wk","text_ar":"شوك"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S:) and accord. to AZ, one says also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAkK fiY","text_ar":"شَاكٍ فِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~ilAHi","text_ar":"السِّلاحِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$wk","text_ar":"شوك"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~aAkiY","text_ar":"الشَّاكِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[is app. formed in like manner from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~aAy^iku","text_ar":"الشَّايِكُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and] signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The lion."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["S"]},{"entry_id":"n23356","headword_ar":"شَاكٌ","root":"$wk","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"; and its fem., with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAy^ikN","text_ar":"شَايِكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in four places."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}